    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My mother adamantly hates the things and so I always assumed they were vile.  One day while passing through the farmers market with my 4 year old daughter, we saw a mound of locally grown brussel sprouts near the fresh green beans, a mandatory stop.  My daughter begged me to get some of the baby cabbages.  </></>What kind of dad would I be if I didn&#8217;t buy my kid brussel sprouts when she cries for them?  So we brought them home and steamed them with some vinager and mustard.  Now they are a family favorite.</p>
    </div>

