      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=1703#comment-3098"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-01-09T03:51:28-05:00">Sunday, January 9, 2011 at 3:51 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Alison, I&#39;m sorry to hear that this recipe wasn&#39;t a success for you!  Say, do you ever squeeze a little lemon juice on your roasted Brussels sprouts?  I&#39;ve been doing that lately, and it really perks them up and balances their flavor.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=1703#comment-3098' data-commentid="3098" data-postid="1703" data-belowelement="comment-3098" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Molly" aria-label='Reply to Molly'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-3099" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/11569259623653346482" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Alison</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=1703#comment-3099"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-01-09T15:51:04-05:00">Sunday, January 9, 2011 at 3:51 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Absolutely. Lemon makes many things better. But my favorite way to eat roasted brussel sprouts is with a bit of maple syrup, cider vinegar, and mustard. mmmmmm. I want to try the cream-braised brussel sprouts you posted but it may be a while before my hips can stand it.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=1703#comment-3099' data-commentid="3099" data-postid="1703" data-belowelement="comment-3099" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alison" aria-label='Reply to Alison'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-60512" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
